text: Those who excel reach the stars
Manhattan School of Music is one of the world's premier music conservatories for classical music, jazz, and musical theatre.
Choose an academic program, discover our exceptional faculty, or come hear one of more than 600 live concerts a year at our campus and around NYC.
“At MSM we promote the highest standards of excellence in our supportive atmosphere, infused with the incomparable creative energy of New York City.”
Robert Mann String Quartet Institute: JAN 9-12, 2020
Trombone Master Class with Matthew Gee
Faculty Recital: Jeremy McCoy, double bass
Stay On It: Julius Eastman and M. Lamar, MSM Student Project in Performance
“I Want to Sing My Heart Out in Praise of Life”: The Kusama Suite, MSM Student Project in Performance
Paul Watkins Cello Masterclass in Ades Performance Space
Dora Zaslavsky Koch Competition in Greenfield Hall
Timpani Recital Coordinated by Duncan Patton
In this vibrant program for young musicians age 8-17, students develop their musical skills and join a vibrant community. Applications due January 15, 2020.
A musical holiday greeting from Manhattan School of Music!
Please enjoy our spirited interpretation of "Winter Wonderland," and many thanks to the more than 145 students who took part!
MSM Spotlight: Voice students Joanne Evans (MM ’21) and Blair Cagney (BM ’18, MM ’20)
Masters students Joanne and Blair are featured cast members in MSM Opera Theater’s colorful and comical production of Saverio Mercadante's "I due Figaro", December 12–15 in Niedorff-Karpati Hall.
Visit our Admissions page to learn more.
